data.name: Lasertracker
data.description: Active coordinate measurement device based on laser interferometry for Large-Scale metrology applications.

parameters.name: State
parameters.description: The current state of the device.

functions.name: Reset
functions.description: Resets the device into the state like directly after start-up.

components.name: Base Stations
components.description: Object acting as a list of base stations of the metrology system.

components.name: Base
components.description: Represents a base station in a distributed system.

measurements.name: Position
measurements.description: Position of the base of the tracker within a global reference frame.

measurements.name: Quaternion
measurements.description: Orientation of the base in relation to the orientation of a global reference frame.

measurements.name: Azimuth
measurements.description: Current position of azimuth rotation encoder in Radian.

measurements.name: Elevation
measurements.description: Current position of elevation rotation encoder in Radian.

measurements.name: Distance
measurements.description: Measured distance to the currently activate target.

parameters.name: State
parameters.description: The current state of the device.

functions.name: Jog
functions.description: Jogs the tracker head by the given angles for the azimuth and elevation.

arguments.name: Azimuth
arguments.description: Current position of azimuth rotation encoder in Radian.

arguments.name: Elevation
arguments.description: Current position of elevation rotation encoder in Radian.

functions.name: Point to
functions.description: Moves the tracker head so that the laser points to the specified position.

components.name: Mobile Entities
components.description: Object acting as a list of mobile entities in the metrology system.

measurements.name: Quaternion
measurements.description: Most recently dispatched measured orientation as quaternion, if available.

measurements.name: Locked
measurements.description: Boolean flag specifying whether the target is locked in.

parameters.name: State
parameters.description: Reflects the current state of the target. If logged in: OK. If not stable: WARNING. If lost: ERROR.

parameters.name: Mode
parameters.description: Current state of the entity. In CONTINUOUS mode, values are dispatched as fast as possible. In TRIGGERED mode, values are only dispatches after a software trigger. In EXTERNAL mode, values are dispatched in accordance to an external trigger, e.g. probe or TTL. IDLE means the entity is currently not used.

parameters.name: Type
parameters.description: System specific identifier of the target Type, e.g. SMR or Active SMR.

functions.name: Reset
functions.description: Starts the search routine around the current direction.

functions.name: Trigger
functions.description: Trigger count variables and set the resulting label. This function is only allowed in triggered acquisition mode.
